1
00:00:12,616 --> 00:00:14,285
-Nicky.
-What?

2
00:00:14,368 --> 00:00:15,703
Everyone's dead.

3
00:00:16,746 --> 00:00:17,580
I know that.

4
00:00:17,663 --> 00:00:19,081
Well, why didn't they kill us?

5
00:00:19,165 --> 00:00:21,625
I don't care. We've got to go.

6
00:00:21,709 --> 00:00:23,878
But it could mean something.
We should call someone.

7
00:00:23,961 --> 00:00:25,421
-Like who? The police?
-Uh…

8
00:00:25,504 --> 00:00:27,923
"Hi, this crazy thing happened
at the hotel that we're at,

9
00:00:28,007 --> 00:00:29,467
and we're the only ones left alive."

10
00:00:29,550 --> 00:00:32,470
"By the way, don't you dare ask
a single follow-up question"?

11
00:00:32,553 --> 00:00:33,929
-What the fuck?
-Okay, I'm sorry.

12
00:00:34,013 --> 00:00:36,849
I had one reactive thought
to witnessing a massacre. I'm sorry.

13
00:00:36,932 --> 00:00:39,518
We have to go. We have to start moving.

14
00:00:39,602 --> 00:00:43,397
Watch where you're stepping!
There is blood everywhere!

15
00:00:43,481 --> 00:00:44,774
I am. I am.

16
00:00:51,614 --> 00:00:52,990
You should go home.

17
00:00:53,783 --> 00:00:54,950
Okay.

18
00:00:55,034 --> 00:00:57,286
Nicky, Nicky, I don't think those guys
work at the hotel.

19
00:00:57,369 --> 00:00:58,788
No shit, Morgan.

20
00:01:07,630 --> 00:01:09,548
I don't understand what's taking so long.

21
00:01:09,632 --> 00:01:12,384
They should've called with
the election results half an hour ago.

22
00:01:12,468 --> 00:01:14,303
Clearly, it wasn't a landslide,

23
00:01:14,386 --> 00:01:17,139
which frankly, says more
about the people of this town

24
00:01:17,223 --> 00:01:19,016
than it does our campaign.

25
00:01:19,100 --> 00:01:21,852
You know, Susan Gopnik stopped me
in the grocery store

26
00:01:21,936 --> 00:01:25,064
to say that she voted for me.
I could tell that she was lying.

27
00:01:25,147 --> 00:01:28,317
Her mother was arrested for shoplifting
when we were in high school.

28
00:01:28,400 --> 00:01:30,653
Woman is a sociopath.

29
00:01:30,736 --> 00:01:32,238
Natalie!

30
00:01:32,321 --> 00:01:34,073
Natalie!

31
00:01:34,156 --> 00:01:35,116
Did you call me?

32
00:01:35,199 --> 00:01:38,285
Honey, blender's a little loud.
I can't hear myself think.

33
00:01:38,369 --> 00:01:41,038
-Copy-copy.
-What are you two so quiet about?

34
00:01:43,082 --> 00:01:45,501
Oh, should we be talking about something
while we wait?

35
00:01:45,584 --> 00:01:47,711
I'm nervous… for you.

36
00:01:47,795 --> 00:01:50,881
Well, that's hardly a useful way
to spend your time.

37
00:01:50,965 --> 00:01:54,051
You go down to Miami,
the both of you, on a church retreat,

38
00:01:54,135 --> 00:01:55,761
come back looking like fresh death.

39
00:01:55,845 --> 00:01:57,513
That's kind of you, Ma.

40
00:01:57,596 --> 00:01:59,849
Natalie! Honey!

41
00:01:59,932 --> 00:02:01,892
I'm begging you, if you love me,

42
00:02:01,976 --> 00:02:04,562
you will make that smoothie
any other time but now!

43
00:02:05,771 --> 00:02:07,648
-Here you are.
-Thank you, hon.

44
00:02:07,731 --> 00:02:10,025
-Yeah.
-Mmm. Mm-mm-mm.

45
00:02:11,944 --> 00:02:15,906
So I just want to tell you all
how much these past couple of months

46
00:02:15,990 --> 00:02:16,991
have meant to me.

47
00:02:17,074 --> 00:02:21,162
Natalie, you have steered me
through this election

48
00:02:21,245 --> 00:02:25,166
with a poise and a maturity
well beyond your years.

49
00:02:26,041 --> 00:02:28,002
And watching the two of you,

50
00:02:29,170 --> 00:02:31,547
uh, find your way back to each other.

51
00:02:31,630 --> 00:02:34,884
I just want to say,
no matter what happens today,

52
00:02:34,967 --> 00:02:38,012
this family will always be
my guiding light.

53
00:02:38,095 --> 00:02:40,181
Mm.

54
00:02:43,642 --> 00:02:45,269
It's an unlisted number.

55
00:02:45,352 --> 00:02:46,312
Answer it!

56
00:02:47,313 --> 00:02:48,772
Linda Morelli.

57
00:02:49,565 --> 00:02:50,608
Mm-hmm.

58
00:02:51,901 --> 00:02:53,777
Okay. Okay.

59
00:02:55,946 --> 00:02:56,947
Right.

60
00:02:57,907 --> 00:02:59,742
I understand. Thank you.

61
00:03:05,998 --> 00:03:07,291
What?

62
00:03:08,459 --> 00:03:09,835
Hm.

63
00:03:19,178 --> 00:03:21,388
We lost, didn't we?

64
00:03:22,139 --> 00:03:23,474
We tied.

65
00:03:23,974 --> 00:03:25,184
Tied?

66
00:03:25,267 --> 00:03:26,810
-Well…
-What?

67
00:03:26,894 --> 00:03:30,689
No, now, don't second-guess yourself.
We did everything that we could.

68
00:03:30,773 --> 00:03:33,442
Okay. Mm-hmm.
So, n-- now what? What do we do?

69
00:03:33,525 --> 00:03:39,031
Well, according to the council,
it comes down to a game of chance.

70
00:03:39,114 --> 00:03:43,953
-No! Mom! Oh my God!
-Honey. Natalie. Natalie.

71
00:03:44,036 --> 00:03:44,870
Stop.

72
00:03:44,954 --> 00:03:47,581
What, it's like, being decided
by drawing straws?

73
00:03:47,665 --> 00:03:49,416
-Mom! No! No!
-Honey.

74
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:51,585
Oh my God, this is insane!

75
00:03:51,669 --> 00:03:54,755
Three days checking the news, nothing.

76
00:03:54,838 --> 00:03:57,383
Whole room of people gets killed,
nobody's talking about it.

77
00:03:57,466 --> 00:03:58,968
Well, it's clearly been covered up.

78
00:03:59,051 --> 00:04:00,511
I'm well aware of that, okay?

79
00:04:00,594 --> 00:04:04,682
But I have a very bad feeling
that they're coming for us.

80
00:04:04,765 --> 00:04:06,684
We were forced into this, you know?

81
00:04:06,767 --> 00:04:10,604
Two upstanding citizens going missing
is probably not worth the hassle for them.

82
00:04:10,688 --> 00:04:12,898
-Yeah.
-You know, if they wanted us dead,

83
00:04:12,982 --> 00:04:15,150
they had their chance. They let us go.

84
00:04:15,234 --> 00:04:17,403
That is what I'm choosing
to believe, okay?

85
00:04:17,486 --> 00:04:18,862
What's the alternative?

86
00:04:18,946 --> 00:04:21,240
They kill us some other time.

87
00:04:22,366 --> 00:04:25,536
That's an upper.
That's a good-- That's good.

88
00:04:27,079 --> 00:04:29,039
It's over. We tied.

89
00:04:29,123 --> 00:04:30,916
How is that possible?

90
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:33,627
Susan fucking Gopnik, that's how.

91
00:04:48,642 --> 00:04:50,311
-Hi.
-Hi.

92
00:04:50,936 --> 00:04:53,355
I hope I'm not interrupting
your flow with God.

93
00:04:53,439 --> 00:04:56,692
I think he's thrilled that I'm leaving,
to be honest.

94
00:04:56,775 --> 00:04:58,068
So it's official?

95
00:04:58,152 --> 00:05:01,488
Uh, yeah. It was a joint decision.

96
00:05:02,281 --> 00:05:04,074
-Wow.
-It's nice to see you.

97
00:05:04,158 --> 00:05:05,826
Yeah.

98
00:05:06,410 --> 00:05:07,953
I think…

99
00:05:08,037 --> 00:05:09,538
-Can I go first?
-Uh-huh.

100
00:05:11,874 --> 00:05:14,043
I owe you a thank-you.

101
00:05:14,960 --> 00:05:16,628
I don't know who those kids were,

102
00:05:16,712 --> 00:05:19,131
but they managed
to get most of the money back.

103
00:05:19,631 --> 00:05:20,632
Sorry, what kids?

104
00:05:20,716 --> 00:05:23,761
Those hacker kids
in your Sunday school who found Tegan.

105
00:05:23,844 --> 00:05:27,306
-Oh. That's right. The hackers…
-The Hackers for Christ or whatever.

106
00:05:27,389 --> 00:05:30,059
Yeah, I don't want to know
how they did it, but…

107
00:05:30,934 --> 00:05:33,771
They restored my faith in Gen Alpha.

108
00:05:35,606 --> 00:05:37,983
Happy to help.

109
00:05:38,067 --> 00:05:42,237
Yeah, you helped, despite me blaming you,
which you shouldn't have had to do.

110
00:05:42,321 --> 00:05:43,364
Hmm.

111
00:05:44,656 --> 00:05:46,241
I would really like a fresh start.

112
00:05:46,950 --> 00:05:48,869
Everything out in the open.

113
00:05:48,952 --> 00:05:49,995
No more hiding.

114
00:05:55,209 --> 00:05:57,961
There's something that I want to tell you.

115
00:05:58,045 --> 00:05:59,088
Of course.

116
00:05:59,171 --> 00:06:00,172
I'm here.

117
00:06:00,756 --> 00:06:02,174
You can tell me anything.

118
00:06:04,468 --> 00:06:05,594
Mm.

119
00:06:07,012 --> 00:06:08,305
Let's go for a walk.

120
00:06:08,806 --> 00:06:09,723
Yeah?

121
00:06:09,807 --> 00:06:11,266
-Okay. Yeah.
-Okay.

122
00:06:13,977 --> 00:06:16,563
Are we going to party?
Three handles of whiskey?

123
00:06:16,647 --> 00:06:18,649
If we wanted this much,
we should've gone to Costco.

124
00:06:18,732 --> 00:06:21,527
Okay, I didn't say anything when you put
Lucky Charms and juice boxes in.

125
00:06:21,610 --> 00:06:23,320
Feels like I'm shopping
with a six-year-old.

126
00:06:23,404 --> 00:06:26,657
My juice boxes are for after my workouts,
and you also eat Lucky Charms.

127
00:06:26,740 --> 00:06:29,952
God, you've been such,
like, a grumpy old witch lately.

128
00:06:32,746 --> 00:06:35,249
Oh, no, don't worry, I got it.
I got these.

129
00:07:12,870 --> 00:07:14,288
Fuck, Max!

130
00:07:14,371 --> 00:07:15,747
Fuck.

131
00:07:15,831 --> 00:07:16,915
Morgan!

132
00:07:17,749 --> 00:07:18,584
Morgan!

133
00:07:18,667 --> 00:07:20,919
Oh my God, oh my God. Fuck.

134
00:07:21,003 --> 00:07:23,046
-I'm so sorry. Are you okay?
-You fucking ran me over!

135
00:07:23,130 --> 00:07:25,424
I know. It was a mistake.
Okay, do you need an ambulance?

136
00:07:25,507 --> 00:07:26,425
No, I'm fine.

137
00:07:26,508 --> 00:07:29,344
-I'm stuck, okay? Just pull me out.
-Give me your hands. Come on.

138
00:07:29,428 --> 00:07:31,138
-Pull. Pull.
-Ah, give it a little kick.

139
00:07:31,221 --> 00:07:33,182
-Okay.
-Pull.

140
00:07:33,265 --> 00:07:34,766
-Ow. Fuck. Ow, ow, ow.
-Oh my God. Okay.

141
00:07:34,850 --> 00:07:37,478
-There's, like, an undercarriage on me.
-The carriage is on you?

142
00:07:37,561 --> 00:07:39,521
-Yeah, it's on my femur muscle.
-Fuck. Okay.

143
00:07:39,605 --> 00:07:42,191
-Okay, I'm going to ask someone for help.
-No, Morgan, fuck!

144
00:07:42,274 --> 00:07:44,485
-What?
-This is really fucking embarrassing.

145
00:07:44,568 --> 00:07:45,444
Oh my God.

146
00:07:45,527 --> 00:07:47,738
Oh my God. People are getting out
of their fucking cars!

147
00:07:47,821 --> 00:07:50,407
-Okay, hey. Gu-- guys, he is okay.
-Tell them to go away.

148
00:07:50,491 --> 00:07:51,575
Please go away.

149
00:07:51,658 --> 00:07:53,827
I'm so fucking mad at you,
it's giving me a headache.

150
00:07:53,911 --> 00:07:55,621
Seriously? You're filming?

151
00:07:55,704 --> 00:07:57,998
He said it was hiding in plain sight.

152
00:07:58,081 --> 00:07:59,374
He left the key in the lock.

153
00:07:59,458 --> 00:08:03,295
I don't know. I don't run
an illegal import-export business.

154
00:08:03,378 --> 00:08:05,506
And that led to a room of people
being murdered?

155
00:08:05,589 --> 00:08:09,843
No, that led to us getting involved.
I think the… the murders

156
00:08:09,927 --> 00:08:13,555
had more to do with the hundreds
of thousands of dollars' worth of cocaine

157
00:08:13,639 --> 00:08:16,350
that were being illegally imported
in a cow's testicles.

158
00:08:16,433 --> 00:08:19,269
-Okay, do you hear yourself right now?
-Yeah, of course I hear myself.

159
00:08:19,353 --> 00:08:22,356
Okay, what now then?
Are people out there looking for you?

160
00:08:24,608 --> 00:08:25,776
I don't know. I don't--

161
00:08:25,859 --> 00:08:28,570
-I don't-- I don't think so.
-You don't think so?

162
00:08:28,654 --> 00:08:30,906
Well, that feels like
a pretty important thing to know,

163
00:08:30,989 --> 00:08:33,200
considering I'm standing
right beside you, Nick.

164
00:08:33,283 --> 00:08:35,619
-I'm sleeping at your house.
-You told me to open up to you.

165
00:08:35,702 --> 00:08:38,580
And… and to tell you the truth.
That's what I've done. This is the truth.

166
00:08:38,664 --> 00:08:40,374
Well, of course I wanted the truth.

167
00:08:40,457 --> 00:08:42,793
I just wasn't necessarily expecting
to hear that my boyfriend

168
00:08:42,876 --> 00:08:44,795
was at the center of a mass murder.

169
00:08:44,878 --> 00:08:46,213
God. I did it for us.

170
00:08:46,296 --> 00:08:48,298
How does this have anything to do with us?

171
00:08:51,468 --> 00:08:54,054
How do you think you got your money back?

172
00:08:54,137 --> 00:08:55,514
The Hackers for Christ.

173
00:08:57,474 --> 00:09:00,018
-Okay.
-There are no Hackers for Christ.

174
00:09:00,102 --> 00:09:02,896
Of course there aren't
any "Hackers for Christ."

175
00:09:03,647 --> 00:09:06,233
I had to do a favor
in exchange for a favor.

176
00:09:07,234 --> 00:09:09,861
Are you seriously putting
the murder of 15 people on me?

177
00:09:09,945 --> 00:09:11,029
Are you seriously thinking

178
00:09:11,113 --> 00:09:13,282
that I'm putting
the murder of 15 people on you?

179
00:09:13,365 --> 00:09:16,827
Do I look like I know what to think?

180
00:09:20,497 --> 00:09:22,207
Take it. I'll keep walking.

181
00:09:28,505 --> 00:09:31,091
-I can't really talk right now.
-Did your flip phone ring?

182
00:09:31,174 --> 00:09:32,634
What? Uh, I don't know.

183
00:09:32,718 --> 00:09:34,428
I haven't looked at it since Miami.

184
00:09:34,511 --> 00:09:35,637
Because mine did.

185
00:09:38,015 --> 00:09:40,100
Wh… How?

186
00:09:40,183 --> 00:09:42,769
-I don't know. I didn't pick up.
-Well, don't!

187
00:09:42,853 --> 00:09:45,439
Throw it in the fucking ocean.
I don't care. Just get rid of it.

188
00:09:45,522 --> 00:09:46,815
Dr. Flores…

189
00:09:46,898 --> 00:09:48,609
What is that? Where are you?

190
00:09:48,692 --> 00:09:49,651
Urgent care.

191
00:09:49,735 --> 00:09:51,111
Why? Are you okay?

192
00:09:51,194 --> 00:09:52,487
Yeah, I'm okay.

193
00:09:52,571 --> 00:09:54,114
I ran over Max by accident.

194
00:09:57,701 --> 00:09:59,578
What even is that?

195
00:09:59,661 --> 00:10:01,538
-Rock, paper, scissors?
-Yes.

196
00:10:01,622 --> 00:10:03,332
It-- it's that stupid hand game

197
00:10:03,415 --> 00:10:06,918
Nicky and Morgan used to play to decide
who didn't have to take out the trash.

198
00:10:07,002 --> 00:10:09,046
Well, you want to know
who feels like trash now?

199
00:10:09,129 --> 00:10:12,633
This grown woman who's reduced
to playing a children's game

200
00:10:12,716 --> 00:10:15,052
with that local slime bucket.

201
00:10:15,135 --> 00:10:19,264
Well, you know, at least it's better
than whatever Tom suggested.

202
00:10:19,348 --> 00:10:21,933
Chess isn't even a game of chance.
It's fully strategic.

203
00:10:22,017 --> 00:10:23,769
And misogynistic.

204
00:10:23,852 --> 00:10:26,938
Name a woman who has time for chess.

205
00:10:27,022 --> 00:10:30,484
Natalie, this whole thing
is just so humiliating.

206
00:10:30,567 --> 00:10:34,321
Ugh! I know. I'm pissed off too.

207
00:10:35,238 --> 00:10:40,327
But I think we owe it to ourselves
to show people that

208
00:10:40,410 --> 00:10:43,038
unlike Tom, this isn't just about power.

209
00:10:43,121 --> 00:10:45,582
No, it is about power, Natalie.

210
00:10:45,666 --> 00:10:48,877
It's always about power
when you've never had any.

211
00:10:48,960 --> 00:10:51,588
When I was your age,
I was working in the shop.

212
00:10:51,672 --> 00:10:53,090
Not because I wanted to,

213
00:10:53,173 --> 00:10:55,342
but because it was
just what everybody did.

214
00:10:55,425 --> 00:10:58,553
I didn't have the luxury
of going to grad school

215
00:10:58,637 --> 00:11:01,890
or trying bangs like you, hon.

216
00:11:01,973 --> 00:11:05,185
And then I fell in love with your father,
and that was a wonderful thing

217
00:11:05,268 --> 00:11:07,270
until we wanted kids,

218
00:11:07,354 --> 00:11:10,148
and I found out
that I couldn't have any on my own.

219
00:11:10,232 --> 00:11:13,485
So we adopted your brother
and loved him so much,

220
00:11:13,568 --> 00:11:15,987
and then all of a sudden,
I was pregnant with Morgan.

221
00:11:16,071 --> 00:11:18,782
A miracle, everybody said.

222
00:11:18,865 --> 00:11:21,993
And then eight years later,
you came along, another little miracle.

223
00:11:22,077 --> 00:11:24,913
But the truth is, honey,
you two weren't planned.

224
00:11:24,996 --> 00:11:27,999
You were gifts from God,
so how could I not keep you?

225
00:11:28,083 --> 00:11:29,418
But you weren't planned.

226
00:11:29,501 --> 00:11:32,129
And I love you to death, honey,
but you weren't planned.

227
00:11:32,212 --> 00:11:33,880
-You were a mistake.
-Right, ye-- yeah.

228
00:11:33,964 --> 00:11:37,759
And so even when my body
eventually gave me everything I wanted,

229
00:11:37,843 --> 00:11:40,262
it wasn't on my terms.

230
00:11:40,345 --> 00:11:42,973
And your father and I
were not in a good enough place.

231
00:11:43,056 --> 00:11:46,685
We got divorced,
and even that wasn't what I wanted.

232
00:11:47,644 --> 00:11:52,774
So when I knew that the day would come
when your nonna would be gone,

233
00:11:52,858 --> 00:11:56,611
and there wasn't anybody else
I needed to take care of,

234
00:11:56,695 --> 00:11:58,739
I just thought, well, why not

235
00:11:59,614 --> 00:12:01,283
reach for a little power…

236
00:12:02,325 --> 00:12:06,371
…before you kids have to wipe my ass
in some hospital room?

237
00:12:14,337 --> 00:12:15,338
Well,

238
00:12:16,298 --> 00:12:20,010
then let's prep you to win
that stupid game.

239
00:13:01,593 --> 00:13:02,594
Hello?

240
00:13:08,517 --> 00:13:12,854
If there is anybody here,
I'm not gonna scream. I'm not gonna run.

241
00:13:12,938 --> 00:13:16,191
It's just not who I am, okay?
So let's just get it over with.

242
00:14:07,826 --> 00:14:09,995
I'm telling you,
I will go wherever you want.

243
00:14:10,078 --> 00:14:11,705
I'm just asking that you say it nicely.

244
00:14:11,788 --> 00:14:13,456
-Nicky, Nicky!
-Morgan?!

245
00:14:13,540 --> 00:14:15,917
-What the fuck is going on?
-I don't know.

246
00:14:16,001 --> 00:14:18,086
-What's going on?
-You tell me. I can't see!

247
00:14:18,169 --> 00:14:20,255
-I also can't see.
-Are we gonna die?

248
00:14:20,338 --> 00:14:22,132
-Uh…
-Help! Someone help!

249
00:14:22,215 --> 00:14:24,009
-Fire!
-Help!

250
00:14:24,092 --> 00:14:26,678
-Fire!
-Why are you yelling "fire"?

251
00:14:26,761 --> 00:14:29,431
I read an article that said
people respond better to "fire"

252
00:14:29,514 --> 00:14:31,850
because "help"
doesn't directly pertain to them.

253
00:14:31,933 --> 00:14:33,935
-It's selfish.
-Fine! Fine, fine, fine!

254
00:14:34,019 --> 00:14:36,354
-Fire!
-Fire! Fire! Fire!

255
00:14:36,438 --> 00:14:39,107
-Fire!
-Will you both shut the fuck up?!

256
00:14:40,358 --> 00:14:41,860
-Yusuf?
-Oh my God.

257
00:14:41,943 --> 00:14:45,572
-Are you fucking kidding me?!
-Oh my God.

258
00:14:45,655 --> 00:14:48,241
This is how I hear from you
after you fucking disappear?

259
00:14:49,242 --> 00:14:52,996
I tried calling, but you didn't answer,
so this is your fucking fault, okay?

260
00:14:53,079 --> 00:14:54,080
Oh my God.

261
00:14:54,164 --> 00:14:55,332
Okay, I knew it.

262
00:14:55,415 --> 00:14:57,000
I knew you two hooked up.

263
00:14:57,083 --> 00:14:59,544
-That's fucking gross. That's gross.
-Okay.

264
00:14:59,628 --> 00:15:03,465
If you would have answered my call,
I would have said thank you.

265
00:15:03,548 --> 00:15:05,592
Why? Why would you have said thank you?

266
00:15:05,675 --> 00:15:08,094
I took my power back. I got a promotion.

267
00:15:08,178 --> 00:15:10,555
Hm. Who did you get a promotion from?
'Cause Ivan's dead.

268
00:15:10,680 --> 00:15:12,891
What the fuck are you two talking about?

269
00:15:12,974 --> 00:15:16,478
Ivan had no power, okay?
I went to his boss.

270
00:15:17,062 --> 00:15:18,271
Who's his fucking boss?

271
00:15:18,355 --> 00:15:19,522
The Italians.

272
00:15:20,357 --> 00:15:21,900
Until he tried to fuck them over,

273
00:15:21,983 --> 00:15:23,985
so I told them
what the fuck was happening in Miami.

274
00:15:24,069 --> 00:15:26,738
Ivan was working for the Mob?

275
00:15:26,821 --> 00:15:29,157
You almost had us fucking killed!

276
00:15:29,240 --> 00:15:30,325
How did I do that?

277
00:15:30,408 --> 00:15:31,576
-How?
-Oh my God.

278
00:15:31,660 --> 00:15:37,123
You being a little tattletale
resulted in a literal massacre, okay?

279
00:15:37,207 --> 00:15:41,670
The Italians killed, like, 15 people.
You're a fucking tattletale!

280
00:15:41,753 --> 00:15:42,796
Mm-hmm.

281
00:15:44,089 --> 00:15:45,507
I'm not a fucking tattletale.

282
00:15:45,590 --> 00:15:48,718
Yeah, you are.
You're a little tattletale snitch, okay?

283
00:15:48,802 --> 00:15:50,845
-And a murderer.
-I'm not a fucking snitch.

284
00:15:50,929 --> 00:15:52,639
-Yes, you are.
-What are you talking about?

285
00:15:52,722 --> 00:15:56,393
-They said just Ivan and Andrei.
-Well, they fucking lied to you, okay?

286
00:15:56,476 --> 00:15:59,980
Because I watched a cartel member
get a bullet in the eye.

287
00:16:00,063 --> 00:16:01,523
Do you know what that sounds like?

288
00:16:01,606 --> 00:16:04,025
They shot up the whole room, Yusuf.
Wake up!

289
00:16:07,779 --> 00:16:08,822
What the fuck.

290
00:16:11,032 --> 00:16:12,325
Both of them here?

291
00:16:14,327 --> 00:16:15,954
Yeah, they're here.

292
00:16:23,336 --> 00:16:25,255
Yusuf, you gonna introduce us?

293
00:16:25,338 --> 00:16:29,300
Yeah, that's Nicky and Morgan.

294
00:16:29,884 --> 00:16:31,344
That's the intro?

295
00:16:31,428 --> 00:16:33,263
Not gonna lie. Needs some work.

296
00:16:37,600 --> 00:16:40,270
We have a question about Miami.

297
00:16:40,353 --> 00:16:41,688
We didn't, um…

298
00:16:41,771 --> 00:16:44,733
-We didn't do anything wrong.
-You didn't do anything wrong?

299
00:16:44,816 --> 00:16:47,986
You helped broker a deal
for 100 kilos of coke.

300
00:16:48,069 --> 00:16:49,112
Hm.

301
00:16:49,195 --> 00:16:54,075
We had eyes on that stupid Russian fuck's
entire Miami circus from start to finish.

302
00:16:54,159 --> 00:16:57,662
Except for a five-minute period
in the bathroom

303
00:16:57,746 --> 00:17:01,416
with the son of the leader
of the Brazilian cartel.

304
00:17:03,710 --> 00:17:04,753
And you.

305
00:17:07,505 --> 00:17:09,257
Nicky. Nicky?

306
00:17:10,341 --> 00:17:13,053
-What are they talking about?
-I… I… I don't know. It was nothing.

307
00:17:13,136 --> 00:17:14,471
He was having a personal crisis.

308
00:17:14,554 --> 00:17:17,474
What crisis required a private audience?

309
00:17:17,557 --> 00:17:19,559
I know it sounds suspicious, okay?

310
00:17:19,642 --> 00:17:22,062
But it has nothing to do with the cartel.

311
00:17:22,145 --> 00:17:24,856
I am a pastor, okay?

312
00:17:24,939 --> 00:17:28,026
He was coming to me
for sp-- spiritual help.

313
00:17:36,785 --> 00:17:38,411
What am I supposed to do with this?

314
00:17:38,495 --> 00:17:40,622
Point it at this well-respected pastor,

315
00:17:40,705 --> 00:17:43,708
and if he doesn't answer our questions
to our satisfaction,

316
00:17:43,792 --> 00:17:46,169
by the time we count from ten, shoot him.

317
00:17:46,252 --> 00:17:47,253
Wait, no, okay.

318
00:17:47,337 --> 00:17:48,713
-Can we just talk about this?
-Ten.

319
00:17:50,423 --> 00:17:52,217
What did you and Filipe speak about?

320
00:17:52,300 --> 00:17:55,178
His life. It was… it was personal.
It had nothing to do with his family.

321
00:17:55,261 --> 00:17:57,555
-Nine.
-Will he be taking over for his father?

322
00:17:57,639 --> 00:18:00,183
-I don't know. We didn't talk about that.
-Seven.

323
00:18:00,266 --> 00:18:04,604
I would tell you if any of this had
anything to do with you or his father

324
00:18:04,687 --> 00:18:06,147
or any of this.

325
00:18:06,231 --> 00:18:07,982
I… I swear to God.

326
00:18:08,066 --> 00:18:12,362
-I am a pastor swearing to God.
-Is he telling the truth?

327
00:18:12,445 --> 00:18:14,781
-Are you telling the truth?
-Five.

328
00:18:14,864 --> 00:18:16,991
Why would I not be
telling the truth, Morgan?!

329
00:18:17,075 --> 00:18:18,868
-Four. Three.
-What the fuck?!

330
00:18:18,952 --> 00:18:21,287
Either put a bullet in my head
or believe me.

331
00:18:21,371 --> 00:18:23,540
-But I… I don't know what else to say.
-One.

332
00:18:28,670 --> 00:18:30,255
Fuck it, shoot him.

333
00:18:30,338 --> 00:18:31,381
Are you serious?

334
00:18:31,464 --> 00:18:32,465
Shoot him.

335
00:18:39,055 --> 00:18:40,098
Guys, I can't.

336
00:18:41,141 --> 00:18:42,600
No, no, no, no, no!

337
00:18:48,731 --> 00:18:50,817
Okay, I believe you.

338
00:18:51,359 --> 00:18:54,946
Although if it was up to us, we'd have
loaded the fucking gun just for fun.

339
00:18:58,491 --> 00:19:01,995
I… I'm going on a cruise for six months
with my boyfriend, okay?

340
00:19:02,078 --> 00:19:04,330
You won't-- won't have to worry about me.

341
00:19:04,414 --> 00:19:06,416
I don't think our boss
would be too thrilled to know

342
00:19:06,499 --> 00:19:09,377
that there's some liability out there
cartwheeling onto a cruise ship

343
00:19:09,460 --> 00:19:11,754
with a stranger for the next six months.

344
00:19:11,838 --> 00:19:14,632
You didn't mention any of this
to your little boyfriend…

345
00:19:14,716 --> 00:19:15,550
Tareq.

346
00:19:15,633 --> 00:19:18,553
Tareq, before you booked that cruise,
did you?

347
00:19:22,473 --> 00:19:25,727
I hope you're telling the truth.
Because if you're not,

348
00:19:26,644 --> 00:19:27,604
we'll find you.

349
00:19:28,605 --> 00:19:29,772
We always do.

350
00:19:34,319 --> 00:19:37,197
You'll be hearing from us
sooner than you'd like.

351
00:20:03,890 --> 00:20:06,142
Thank you for not shooting my brother.

352
00:20:06,893 --> 00:20:09,145
Are you fucking kidding me?

353
00:20:09,229 --> 00:20:14,025
He literally kidnapped us,
tied us up, held a gun to my head,

354
00:20:14,108 --> 00:20:17,195
and set up a room full of people
to be slaughtered.

355
00:20:17,278 --> 00:20:19,697
-Okay! Okay! I thought it was nice.
-What is wrong with you?

356
00:20:19,781 --> 00:20:22,533
-I thought it was nice.
-Is this your relationship with men?

357
00:20:22,617 --> 00:20:25,161
-Stop! Are you fucking--
-Constantly letting them off the hook?

358
00:20:25,245 --> 00:20:27,789
-They're all on the hook!
-This makes a lot of sense, Morgan.

359
00:20:27,872 --> 00:20:30,083
It makes sense. You're on the hook.
You're on the hook.

360
00:20:30,166 --> 00:20:33,336
I'm not on the hook.
Shut your goddamn mouth!

361
00:20:34,754 --> 00:20:36,464
Untie me now!

362
00:20:36,547 --> 00:20:37,590
Don't.

363
00:20:54,274 --> 00:20:55,233
Hi.

364
00:20:57,610 --> 00:21:00,655
Nick, you've put me
in an impossible situation here.

365
00:21:01,531 --> 00:21:02,949
I know that. I… I know.

366
00:21:03,032 --> 00:21:04,742
I'm… I'm sorry.

367
00:21:05,493 --> 00:21:06,703
What do we do?

368
00:21:07,495 --> 00:21:09,163
I don't know.

369
00:21:09,247 --> 00:21:12,208
Nick, we're so fucking close.
In a month and a half,

370
00:21:12,292 --> 00:21:14,794
there's a cruise that can take us
out for six months. We'll be--

371
00:21:14,877 --> 00:21:16,546
I can't go on that cruise.

372
00:21:18,298 --> 00:21:19,674
What are you talking about?

373
00:21:20,967 --> 00:21:25,305
I was abducted last night,
and I cannot go on the cruise.

374
00:21:26,639 --> 00:21:28,808
-What?
-I know the guy. It wasn't his fault.

375
00:21:28,891 --> 00:21:30,476
Okay, Nick, I'm sorry. I can't do this.

376
00:21:30,560 --> 00:21:32,437
-I'm sorry, uh--
-You shouldn't have to do this.

377
00:21:32,520 --> 00:21:36,733
There's nothing to do.
There is… nothing to do anymore.

378
00:21:39,027 --> 00:21:40,069
Are you okay?

379
00:21:44,615 --> 00:21:45,783
Yeah, I'm fine.

380
00:21:48,536 --> 00:21:50,538
I… I think
you should still go on the cruise.

381
00:21:50,621 --> 00:21:53,041
I'm not going on the cruise without you.
That's fucking cruel.

382
00:21:53,124 --> 00:21:55,668
It's not cruel. You were planning on going
with or without me.

383
00:21:55,752 --> 00:21:57,337
I… I think you should still go.

384
00:21:59,339 --> 00:22:01,466
You think I should go on the cruise?

385
00:22:02,383 --> 00:22:04,886
Or you're telling me to go on the cruise?

386
00:22:07,764 --> 00:22:10,141
I am telling you

387
00:22:11,809 --> 00:22:14,228
that I think you should go on the cruise.

388
00:22:17,982 --> 00:22:19,525
Nicky, what have you done?

389
00:22:23,863 --> 00:22:25,239
I mean, the fucked-up thing is

390
00:22:25,323 --> 00:22:27,825
I… I… I d-- I don't know exactly
what I've done.

391
00:22:27,909 --> 00:22:29,744
I'd argue I haven't done much.

392
00:22:29,827 --> 00:22:31,287
Well, you've lied, Nick.

393
00:22:33,539 --> 00:22:36,709
And the scary part is
it seems to come so easy to you.

394
00:22:43,424 --> 00:22:44,592
I'm sorry.

395
00:22:46,386 --> 00:22:47,470
Yeah, me too.

396
00:23:06,656 --> 00:23:09,325
Rock, paper, scissors. Win!

397
00:23:09,409 --> 00:23:11,828
Rock, paper, scissors. Yeah!

398
00:23:11,911 --> 00:23:13,871
Rock, paper, scissors. Win!

399
00:23:13,955 --> 00:23:16,332
Morgan, you've thrown rock
five times in a row.

400
00:23:16,416 --> 00:23:18,292
-Yeah.
-You're not even trying.

401
00:23:18,376 --> 00:23:19,794
Rock, paper, scissors. Wi--

402
00:23:20,461 --> 00:23:23,798
You know what? This is ridiculous.
I don't want to do this with that man.

403
00:23:23,881 --> 00:23:27,635
This is all about tricking people.
I have no interest in that.

404
00:23:27,718 --> 00:23:30,221
That's kind of the point of the game.

405
00:23:30,304 --> 00:23:34,100
It always helps to consider
your opponent's perspective, Mrs. Morelli.

406
00:23:35,143 --> 00:23:36,352
Thank you for that, Kevin.

407
00:23:36,436 --> 00:23:38,020
-Mm, Kevin?
-Yes, honey bear?

408
00:23:38,104 --> 00:23:39,730
I got it. Yeah, over there. Back away.

409
00:23:39,814 --> 00:23:42,650
You know, the great thing about flowers

410
00:23:42,733 --> 00:23:46,070
is they work if you win,
and they work if you lose.

411
00:23:46,154 --> 00:23:49,657
Annette, bless you.
Thank you so much for coming. Aw.

412
00:23:49,740 --> 00:23:52,702
-How are you holding up?
-I'm okay, I'm okay.

413
00:23:52,785 --> 00:23:54,454
-Morgan.
-Hello.

414
00:23:56,998 --> 00:23:58,833
-We just have to wait…
-Oh, look.

415
00:24:00,251 --> 00:24:02,879
-Is Tom ready?
-Actually, no, he's not.

416
00:24:02,962 --> 00:24:05,047
I just got off the phone
with Mr. Donaldson,

417
00:24:05,131 --> 00:24:07,133
who informed me he has decided to concede.

418
00:24:08,217 --> 00:24:09,802
With Tom's concession,

419
00:24:09,886 --> 00:24:12,847
the electoral board hereby declares
Linda Morelli our new mayor.

420
00:24:18,478 --> 00:24:20,021
-I'm the…
-Guys!

421
00:24:21,189 --> 00:24:23,232
Oh my God!

422
00:24:23,816 --> 00:24:25,693
Congratulations!

423
00:24:25,776 --> 00:24:28,905
Linda, see, the best person always wins.

424
00:24:28,988 --> 00:24:31,782
-Oh my God.
-How about a drink? Or six?

425
00:24:31,866 --> 00:24:33,326
Or six.

426
00:24:33,409 --> 00:24:34,744
Honey!

427
00:24:35,870 --> 00:24:37,622
Oh my God.

428
00:24:43,127 --> 00:24:46,797
The wheel of fortune

429
00:24:55,389 --> 00:24:56,307
Hey.

430
00:24:56,390 --> 00:24:58,893
-Congratulations, Linda.
-Oh, thank you.

431
00:24:58,976 --> 00:25:01,729
-I didn't expect to see you here.
-Wouldn't miss it.

432
00:25:05,900 --> 00:25:08,110
-Everything okay?
-Yeah, I'm just happy for you.

433
00:25:08,194 --> 00:25:10,321
Oh, that's really kind of you, honey.

434
00:25:10,404 --> 00:25:13,241
You know, Natalie might appreciate
a hug like that as well.

435
00:25:13,324 --> 00:25:15,201
-Mm. Uh… Yeah.
-Okay.

436
00:25:15,284 --> 00:25:19,539
-Are we close like that? I can't tell.
-Well, let's just get it. Okay.

437
00:25:21,249 --> 00:25:22,792
Oh, what's that? Oh.

438
00:25:25,711 --> 00:25:28,548
The doctor said
you didn't have to wear that all day.

439
00:25:28,631 --> 00:25:30,591
Yeah, Morgan.
I'm trying to get back in the gym,

440
00:25:30,675 --> 00:25:32,593
and the doctors don't have whiplash, so…

441
00:25:33,594 --> 00:25:36,973
Jesus. Next church retreat
should be an AA meeting.

442
00:25:37,056 --> 00:25:39,976
Oh, my one and only child.

443
00:25:40,059 --> 00:25:41,686
Is that really necessary?

444
00:25:42,603 --> 00:25:43,980
-Yes.
-Okay.

445
00:25:44,063 --> 00:25:45,731
-How are you feeling?
-Better.

446
00:25:45,815 --> 00:25:48,609
It only really hurts,
like, when I move my neck.

447
00:25:48,693 --> 00:25:51,070
Aw. Look at the two of you.

448
00:25:51,904 --> 00:25:54,407
If you can get through
running over your partner,

449
00:25:54,490 --> 00:25:56,450
well, you can get through almost anything.

450
00:25:56,534 --> 00:25:58,536
-Am I right?
-Cheers to that, yeah.

451
00:25:58,619 --> 00:26:00,246
You know, when Max was a baby,

452
00:26:00,329 --> 00:26:03,958
his father forgot him in his carrier
on the roof of the car.

453
00:26:04,041 --> 00:26:06,127
Drove halfway down the block
before he realized it.

454
00:26:06,210 --> 00:26:07,295
Oh my God.

455
00:26:07,378 --> 00:26:09,046
We miss your daddy every day.

456
00:26:10,047 --> 00:26:12,174
-Don't we, baby?
-Yeah, we do.

457
00:26:12,758 --> 00:26:14,427
Hey, can I grab you for a minute?

458
00:26:14,510 --> 00:26:16,679
I have a little something upstairs
I need your help with.

459
00:26:16,762 --> 00:26:18,180
-Yeah.
-Of course, yeah.

460
00:26:18,264 --> 00:26:20,266
-Oh, sorry. Thank you.
-Yeah.

461
00:26:29,108 --> 00:26:30,109
Hm.

462
00:26:31,110 --> 00:26:32,236
Wow.

463
00:26:34,864 --> 00:26:37,366
I can't believe
I've never been in here before.

464
00:26:37,450 --> 00:26:38,618
Neither can I.

465
00:26:43,039 --> 00:26:45,791
I'm so proud of your mother.

466
00:26:45,875 --> 00:26:47,460
Ah, all that hard work.

467
00:26:48,127 --> 00:26:52,923
And I am very happy
that we're going to be in-laws.

468
00:26:53,007 --> 00:26:55,551
Yeah, I'm so happy.

469
00:26:55,635 --> 00:26:57,470
Look.

470
00:26:57,553 --> 00:27:01,682
I know that you're not in love
with my son anymore.

471
00:27:02,266 --> 00:27:06,228
The problem is,
he's very much in love with you.

472
00:27:06,312 --> 00:27:10,983
And I just wanted you to know that
if you had any thoughts about leaving him,

473
00:27:12,234 --> 00:27:13,861
that won't be happening.

474
00:27:17,365 --> 00:27:18,366
Excuse me?

475
00:27:18,449 --> 00:27:20,159
I am telling you

476
00:27:21,118 --> 00:27:24,372
that you will be marrying my son.

477
00:27:29,126 --> 00:27:31,170
[people chattering indistinctly]

478
00:27:36,133 --> 00:27:37,343
[music continues]

479
00:27:40,596 --> 00:27:43,808
-[keys beeping]
-[Annette humming]

480
00:27:43,891 --> 00:27:45,351
[lock clicking]

481
00:27:47,144 --> 00:27:52,191
Oh, you know, I forgot to ask you,
how was your church trip?

482
00:27:52,692 --> 00:27:54,568
I heard it didn't go as planned.

483
00:27:55,152 --> 00:27:58,989
You know, Max would be devastated
if anything should happen to you.

484
00:27:59,573 --> 00:28:01,742
One might go so far as to say that,

485
00:28:02,576 --> 00:28:05,162
well, your engagement to my son

486
00:28:05,246 --> 00:28:09,458
is the only reason
you made it back home at all.

487
00:28:10,000 --> 00:28:11,711
[rapid ticking]

488
00:28:15,089 --> 00:28:17,842
-What the fuck are you doing here?
-Lower your fucking voice.

489
00:28:17,925 --> 00:28:20,803
I don't know what you want from us,
but now is not the time, okay?

490
00:28:20,886 --> 00:28:22,555
Please, leave my family out of this.

491
00:28:22,638 --> 00:28:23,931
